<br>
b.) If there is no need of an item in that a currently owned item is<br>
superior to what has dropped and they would never use the item for their<br>
main in attendance, it should be rolled for by those of the class who can<br>
use the item, who are there, and for whom it would benefit from the use of more, rather than to just be sold or handed to an alt or friend's character. In other words, those who have participated in the raid effort should rightfully benefit first from drops made while they were there.<br>
c.) If a drop item is looted and no one of the class who can use it are<br>
in attendance, the whole party in attendance may roll for the item, provided they have not won another non-class-specific drop item during that raid.<br>
<br>
